 Editor's note: If you have trouble viewing the livestream, please click here.PRETORIA President Jacob Zuma will host the national 2017 Africa Day celebrations at the Sefako Makgatho Presidential Guesthouse in Pretoria on Thursday.Africa Day is celebrated annually on 25 May within the African continent to mark the formation of the Organisation of African Unity (OAU) on 25 May 1963 and the African Union (AU) in 2002, as well as celebrate the continent's progress. President Jacob Zuma, Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa, Ministers and Deputy Ministers show support for Africa Day 2017 celebrations. pic.twitter.com/o0C90aObKM READ: Ten things you need to know about Africa DayThe theme for Africa Month 2017 is The Year of OR Tambo: Building a Better Africa and a Better World .The celebrations will be attended by ambassadors and high commissioners from Africa and abroad.Tweets about #AfricaDay AND(FROM:@KhayaJames since:2017-05-25 until:2017-05-26) eNCA